replies.body:
Hello! 

Mute is for sure a huge help as it prevents you from seeing what the team is saying if you feel that they are being rude. Which could in turn distract you from your game play. It would be better to mute and simply communicate through pings. It would give you a much better chance to win. Its not a good idea to tell the person that you are muting them because it's just a way to egg people on and potentially send them on tilt, which can end up effecting your game in a more negative manner over just muting / ignoring them.

~KittySuppSquad {{sticker:sona-playing}} {{sticker:sg-soraka}}
